definition: not having any special skill/without any qualifications
one/1/single/a (article)/as soon as/entire/whole/all/throughout/"one" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 1)/also pr. [yao1] for greater clarity when spelling out numbers digit by digit
actually/place/classifier for houses, small buildings, institutions etc/that which/particle introducing a relative clause or passive/CL:個|个[ge4]

sentences.english: Jack has become Jack of all trades and master of none.
sentences.chinese: 傑克成了個萬事皆通而一無所長的人。

sentences.english: No, of course Ted's no good at all, not at all.
sentences.chinese: 不，泰德自然是一無所長，沒一點好。

sentences.english: He who is good at finding excuses for his sins is good for nothing else.
sentences.chinese: 擅長爲已以罪找藉口的人，在其他任何事上一無所長。
